<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Closes Embassy in Central African Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
announced today that Germany has temporarily closed its embassy in
the Central African Republic due to the worsening situation there.
</P>
<P>
Bonn also called on German nationals to leave the Central
African Republic and warned against traveling to the country.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the central African country flared up last
week after an initial protest by soldiers against unpaid wages
developed into a fighting against President Ange Patasse.
</P>
<P>
Referring to recent chaos in several countries in the region,
Kinkel said: "The situation in the heart of Africa must not be
allowed to become an African version of the domino theory."
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Thursday, he called on the international
community to intensify their efforts in order to create the
minimum conditions for peace, stability and development in Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
