<HEADLINE> Zhang Jinjing Steals Spotlight at Gymnastics International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Jinjing stole the spotlight
on the third and final day of the China Cup Gymnastics
International Invitational Meet with five golds here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zhang triumphed in the five men's apparatus of horizontal bar,
rings, parallel bars, pommel horse and floor exercises.
</P>
<P>
His teammate Shen Jian shared the top place in the rings at
9.525 points.
</P>
<P>
Vitali Roundnitski of Belaru shared the title with Zhang
Jinjing in the floor exercise with a scoring of 9.375 points.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Leric Cristian won the only other gold in the men's
events, taking the vaulting title at 9.550 points.
</P>
<P>
In the women's section, Chinese Mo Huilan won the balance beam
at 9.812 points while world champion Kui Yuanyuan won the vaulting
in 9.58 points.
</P>
<P>
Meng Fei, who claimed the women's all-around individual crown
for China on Wednesday, shared the floor exercises gold with
Ukraine's Viktoriya Karpenko. Both scored 9.752 points. The two
gymnasts also shared the title in the uneven bars at 9.737
points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
