<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Deputy Prime Minister Leaves for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Defence Teffera Walluwa left here today
for Djibouti to attend the celebrations of the 20th anniversary
of Djibouti's independence day.
</P>
<P>
Djibouti won its independence from France on June 27, 1977.
Bilateral relations between Ethiopia and Djibouti have been
developed steadily in the recent years. The two countries signed an
agreement on friednship and cooperation in October, 1991. Close
to 25 bilateral agreements have been signed between the two
neighboring countries during 1993 and 1996. 
