<HEADLINE> Religious Militia Officers Ambushed in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Commander of the armed wing of
the Islamic Fundamentalist Organization, Hassan Dahir Aweys was
wounded and another religious militia officer killed last night
by unidentified gunmen along the road linking Mogadishu to Baidoa
in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports today, the two officers were leading
AL-Itihad reinforcement militiamen towards Gedo region where
fighting is taking place between their forces and the Marehan
clansmen of Somali National Front (SNF).
</P>
<P>
The AI-Itihad reinforcement unit consisting of three vehicles
and a number of armed men was ambushed by unidentified militiamen
near the airport of Ballidogle, 90km west of Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Militia officials from the fundamentalist group said the
incident was tactfully pre-planned to sabotage what they called
the Holy Jihad against the pagans who invaded Gedo region,
nevertheless independent sources attributed the attack to
banditry activity that persisted in the area for some time.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, international aid agencies in Mogadishu and the
port town of Merca suspended their operations today in a one-day
mourning for the killing of the Portuguese gynecologist doctor in
Baidoa on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese doctor, Ricardo Marques, from the MSF-Portugal
was killed by Somali gunmen, of which one was apprehended in
connection with the killing by Hussein Aidid's local authorities.
</P>
</TEXT>
