<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Clash in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed and
an undetermined number of others wounded in today's intense combat
between government soldiers and Moro Islamic Liberation Front
(MILF) rebels in the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Citing an initial military report, the local television ABS-CBN
said the slain included four soldiers and two civilians.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, MILF Vice Chairman Al Hadj Murad told the television
that the group has decided to postpone its peace talks with the
government scheduled for June 28 and 29 due to the ongoing
fighting in North Cotabato province.
</P>
<P>
But Gen. Arnulfo Acedera, chief of staff of the Armed Forces,
told reporters that the military will continue its ongoing
offensive against the MILF despite the rebels' threat to pull out
from the negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
He said the military will go on with its ground and air attacks
on the positions of the rebels to save the 40 hostages who remain
in the hands of the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Acedera said this new hostage-taking incident was a
diversionary tactic of the MILF to relieve military pressure on
its Rajamuda camp in Pikit town, North Cotabato.
</P>
<P>
Today's conflict broke out at 5:30 a.m. in Kabacan, North
Cotabato, when MILF rebels stopped three buses along a highway
near the town and held hostage some 100 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Sixty hostages were rescued after the military, backed by
helicopter gunships, fought a four-hour battle with the rebels who
used the hostages as human shields.
</P>
<P>
The highway, linking North Cotabato and Davao province, was
reopened at noon and a group of marines were later deployed to
guard it.
</P>
<P>
The government troops are now tracking down the fleeing rebels
in the towns of Carmen and Pikit in North Cotabato.
</P>
<P>
Since early last week, the government troops and the MILF have
fought fierce battles in Pikit town after the MILF separatists
seized 43 oil workers as hostage.
</P>
<P>
The military rescued all the hostages and began to pursue the
MILF kidnappers. Earlier reports said 47 rebels and five soldiers
were killed during the fierce clashes between the MILF and the
military in the past 10 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
