<HEADLINE> New Reductions Made in S.Africa's International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- South African telephone
company Telkom today announced reduced fee rates for international
telephone calls to 29 destinations from July 1.
</P>
<P>
The new reductions see fee rates reduced to countries as far
afield as the United States, Canada, Australia, New Zealand and
Kenya, Telkom spokesman Marius Ochse said.
</P>
<P>
"These reductions form part of a process which kicked off in
April, when international rates were reduced to eight countries,"
Ochse said.
</P>
<P>
Telkom international business Executive Rhynie Greeff said the
reductions would enable South African companies to lower
operating costs, allowing for greater competitiveness in the
global arena.
</P>
<P>
Those with family and friends abroad would also be able to
keep in touch at much more affordable rates. More reductions were
on the cards, Greeff said.
</P>
<P>
"Negotiations with Telkom's international telecommunication
partners are going ahead full steam, and we are confident that we
will be able to announce further rate reductions before the end
of the year," Greeff added. Endtiem

