<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Russia to Pass START-2 Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The visiting U.S. First Deputy
Defense Secretary John White today urged the Russian parliament to
ratify the START-2 treaty as soon as possible, the Itar-Tass News
Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. official said that the ratification will be in the
interests of both the United States and Russia. It does not affect
security interests and will enable advance in discussing START-3
treaty, he added.
</P>
<P>
Besides, other matters of Russo-american relations in the
military-political area, specifically the holding of joint
Russian-U.S. military exercises, were also touched upon by John
White on Wednesday during his meetings with Russian Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev, First Deputy Defense Minister Andrei
Kokoshin, representatives of the Russian States Duma Disarmament
Committee and with staffers of various independent research
institutions in defense and security areas.
</P>
<P>
In replying to a question how the United States call to reduce
arms stockpiles goes along with the creation of a new kind of
nuclear weapons, White said that his country does not conduct
nuclear weapon tests and keeps from developing new types of
nuclear armaments. 
</P>
