<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian journalists have been
urged to pay prime attention to drug abuse and drug trafficking
in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the call came today from
a workshop on the role of the mass media on the prevention of the
drug abuse organized by the Ethiopian Health Ministry at Nazareth,
some 90 km from here.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a 5-day workshop, Beyene Seiletsion, Head of
Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Sub Control Division in the
Ministry of Health, said most government officials are not aware
that drug abuse and drug trafficking have become serious in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
