and allow a president to be manipulated as people were killed or
maimed."
</P>
<P>
The new military leader said Kabbah should have
incorporated Foday Sankoh, leader of the rebel Revolutionary United
Front into his government but had failed to do so.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a report reaching here said the Kamajors,
an ethnic group of traditional hunters who are against the new
military regime killed up to 15 government soldiers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Kamajors attacked the soldiers on the Kono Highway while the
soldiers were on their way to the capital Freetown, the report said.
