<HEADLINE> Geoinformation Urged in Ethiopia's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Science and
Technology Commissioner Asrat Bulbula today stressed the role of
geoinformation in the socio-economic development of Ethiopia, a
local report said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a two-day workshop here attended by over 100 people
from various sectors, Asrat said despite the existence of an
estimated annual runoff of 111 billion cubic meters from
12 major river basins and about 2.6 billion cubic meters of
exploitable ground water resources in the country, only fractions
have been developed so far.
</P>
<P>
"Only about three percent of the 3.5 million hectares of
irrigational land has been utilized and only 26.3 percent of the
population has access to clean and safe water supply," he noted.
</P>
<P>
According to the commissioner, geoinformation is the basic
input for agricultural projects, mineral exploration and
exploitation, development and conservation of water resources,
natural hazards monitoring and reduction, urban development
planning, infrastructure construction and environmental
monitoring and protection. enditem

