Dublin today after winning support from some independent
legislators.
</P>
<P>
Ahern, whose opposition alliance has snatched a cliffhanger
election victory early this month, won a parliamentary vote
against outgoing Prime Minister John Bruton by 85 votes to 78 in
the 166-seat parliament, press reports from Dublin said.
</P>
<P>
