<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing to Back Microenterprise in Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 22.2 million U.S.
dollars in financing for microenterprise credit in Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Some 12,000 loans are expected to be granted to
microentrepreneurs under the program, which could create an
average of 2.5 jobs for each loan.
</P>
<P>
Special attention will be directed toward supporting projects
that will protect the environment and include benefits for women
microentrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
The financing is made up of a 20 million loan in hard
currencies from the IDB's ordinary capital, 2.2 million dollars in
nonreimbursable local currency for technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is 25 million dollars. The local
counterpart will contribute 2.8 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The latest project represents a deepening and expansion of the
successful first phase of a microenterprise credit program which
was supported by a 12 million loan from the IDB approved in 1992.
</P>
