<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Hungary's Energy Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of a 60 million U.S. dollar loan for the quick start
gas turbine project in Hungary.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to provide about 220 MW of additional
generation reserve capacity to allow the country to maintain a
level of reliability and security of supply consistent with the
standards of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the project will help Hungary enhance its role as a
transit country for the electricity trade throughout Europe.
</P>
<P>
The project consists of two complete single cycle gas turbine
power plants rated at about 110 MW each, burning light distillate
fuel oil.
</P>
<P>
After Hungary joined the World Bank in 1982, the bank
commitments total 3.97 billion dollars for 37 projects. 
</P>
