<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Start Full-Scale Repair of Nigerin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KADUNA, NIGERIA (Xinhua) -- The rehabilitation of Nigeria's
3,200-km railway system was put on its high gear today as a
grand ceremony was held to mark the full-scale commencement of
the project.
</P>
<P>
The 526-million-U.S.-dollar project, which also include the
provision of 50 locomotives, 150 passenger cars, 400 wagons and 20
rail cars by the Chinese, is undertaken by the China Civil
Engineering Construction Corportion (CCECC).
</P>
<P>
In his keynote speech at the ceremony, held in this industrial base
in northern Nigeria, Nigerian head of state General Sani Abacha
expressed satisfaction at the progress made so far in the project.
</P>
<P>
He said he is fully convinced of the determination and capability
of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"I believe they can successfully complete the railway
rehabilitation project," Abacha said.
</P>
<P>
Sun Yongfu, Deputy Railways Minister of China, said the Chinese
government and his ministry, aware of the great importance of the
project to Nigeria's economic development, give top priority to it.
</P>
<P>
An official decision has been made to give full support to CCECC so
that it can "muster superior resources and equipment and launch a mass
campaign of construction so as to complete this project with high
quality on schedule".
</P>
<P>
Under the contract between Nigeria's Ministry of Transport and
the CCECC signed in September 1995, the project is to be
completed at the end of September 1998, when trains will be able
to travel at a speed of 60 to 80 km per hour compared with the
current about 40 km.
</P>
<P>
To date, work on survey and designing of the entire railway
network has been over, production of ballast is underway while
progress has been achieved in the rehabilitation in some
sections. Chinese experts have also arrived to give technical
training to the staff of the Nigerian Railway Corportion (NRC)
and part of the locomotives and rolling stocks has been provided.
</P>
<P>
With the help and cooperation with China, said NRC Sole
Administrator G.C. Ilukwe, his corporation is "determined and
impatient to transform the railways at shortest possible time".
</P>
<P>
The NRC will also create a restructured management manned by
active and forward looking managers capable of leading the
corporation into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's Minister of Transport Major-General I.D. Gumel
shared the same view in his speech on the occasion. He said the
revitalization and rehabilitation project is targeted at
establishing "an efficiant railway system capable of providing
effective service to the Nigerian populace at reasonable price".
</P>
<P>
While expressing his thanks to the Chinese government for the
understanding, support and cooperation concerning the project, Gumel
believed that the CCECC will achieve a succeess in it.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the ceremony, General Abacha and other Nigerian
leaders made an inspection trip on a 30-km section of rehabilitated
railway in a China-built train, accompanied by Sun and Chinese
Ambassador to Nigeria Lu Fengding.
</P>
<P>
All the Nigerian leaders thumbed up at the railway and train,
saying that it is an indication of the future railway system and its
service in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
