<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News in Brief on Activities for Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Following are the news in brief
about activities in China's inland areas for the return of Hong
Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Tibetans Hail HK Return
</P>
<P>
These days in the Tibet Autonomous Region, local people have
held various activities in their own ways to greet the coming
return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At today's gathering in Lhasa, the Tibetan capital, the
participants said that the approaching return of Hong Kong has
helped them to see more clearly the counter-revolutionary nature
of the Dalai Lama Clique in splitting the motherland and
disrupting stability in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Monument At Ancestor's Tomb
</P>
<P>
A "Monument to the Return of Hong Kong" is scheduled to be
erected at the Tomb of Huangdi, the legendary ancestor of the
Chinese Nation, on July 1, the day China resumes its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, the first chief executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, wrote an inscription for the
monument.
</P>
<P>
Gong And Drum Troupe Leaves for HK
</P>
<P>
A musical troupe has left Ansai County, in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province, for Hong Kong to perform the famous local gong
and drum dance on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Half of the 140,000 local people in Ansai County are said to be
good at beating drums and gongs, so many local people had applied
to go as members of the troupe to mark the historic occasion.
</P>
<P>
"1997" in Henan
</P>
<P>
A driver in Zhengzhou, the capital of central China's Henan
Province, with the license number "1997" has decides to carry
people for free on July 1, and the local telephone authority is
offering the friendly price of 1,997 yuan for installing a
telephone.
</P>
<P>
Local people have made every effort to tie everything to the
return of Hong Kong. A few days ago, 40 couples had a joint
wedding ceremony beneath the National Flag and the Flag of the
HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Road
</P>
<P>
The government of Wuhan City, the capital of Central China's
Hubei Province, named a downtown street "Hong Kong Road" to mark
the upcoming return of the territory.
</P>
<P>
The road is near a dozen other streets with names from Taiwan
Province like Taipei Road and Kaohsiung Road.
</P>
<P>
Grand Performance
</P>
<P>
Over 1,300 professional and amateur artists performed in front
of an audience of more than 5,000 this evening in Hangzhou City,
the capital of Zhejiang Province, to greet the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The performance, "Celebrating Hong Kong's Return, Chanting For
the Motherland," was broadcast live across the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
