<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Hold Spectacular to Celebrate SAR First Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Everything is ready for the Hong
Kong 97 Spectacular, the largest live show ever produced on water
in Hong Kong, the Better Hong Kong Foundation announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
"At present, everything is on schedule, the 31 barges and all
the production equipment have arrived and undergone final
installation and trials, said Leonie Ki, chief executive of the
Better Hong Kong Foundation.
</P>
<P>
on the night of July 1, 1997, a flotilla of 31 fully
illuminated barges, in various lively forms and shapes, will be
parading around the Victoria Harbor, amidst colorful water
fountains, lasers and lights, and fireworks to form the climax of
the "Hong Kong 97 Spectacular".
</P>
<P>
At 9:00 p.m., the spectacular begins with Pearl of the Orient,
a tribute to Hong Kong's glamorous international reputation,
performed in music, water fountains, searchlights, lasers and
special effects.
</P>
<P>
Then, the decorative and neon lights of the 140 high-rises
along the waterfront will begin to turn dim slowly as the first of
31 illuminated barges begins its parade around the harbor in the
sea of life section.
</P>
<P>
The barges feature artistic lantern decorations made by the
renowned lantern craftsmen of Foshan. They include the Mighty
Dragon, the biggest lantern ever made by traditional handicraft,
measuring about 40 meters long and 18 meters high and carrying
more than 2,200 light bulbs, she said.
</P>
<P>
The would-be-record-breaking Karaoke will allow millions of
local people to sing with one voice a medley of seven Chinese
songs, which include the "Pearl of the Orient", the New Moon",
"Under the Lion Rock", "Red Cotton Tree", "Tomorrow will Be Better
Day", "Children of the Dragon" and "China's Dream".
</P>
<P>
The sponsors have already distributed 200,000 copies of the
lyrics for the karaoke.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, lasers will dance upon screens of water shooting
out of the Pearl Barge. Boats with fountains of fireworks will set
out from both sides of the harbor and meet, creating a symbolic
bridge linking China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The grand climax of the Hong Kong 97 Spectacular will be
celebration, when Hong Kong's harbor will explode in its
biggest-over pyrotechnics display. This colorful tribute to Hong
Kong will feature 20 tons of fireworks.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, will join some 2,000 distinguished guests
and residents in Hong Kong to view the show from the promenade of
the new extension to the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
The spectacular was initiated by the Better Hong Kong
Foundation, which has raised 100 million HK dollar within a short
period with the support of local industrial and business circles.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
