<HEADLINE> Chinese Red Cross Society Announcement On Hong Kong Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Executive Vice President Gu Yingqi
of the Red Cross Society of China told the International
Federation of the Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies and the
International Committee of the Red Cross in Geneva recently that
the Red Cross Society of China will accept the Hong Kong Red
Cross as a regional branch with a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
According to an announcement of the Red Cross Society of China,
as China resumes the exercise of its sovereignty over Hong Kong at
zero hour of July 1, the Hong Kong Red Cross relations with the UK
counterpart ends at 24:00 hours of June 30.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR, the Statutes
of the International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement, and the
Constitution of the International Federation of Red Cross and Red
Crescent Societies, the Red Cross Society of China has decided to
give the Hong Kong organization branch statues and to call it "the
Red Cross of the Hong Kong SAR of the People's Republic of China".
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Red Cross will use the emblem of the Red Cross
Society of China. The Hong Kong Red Cross can draft and revise its
own constitution and regulations as long as they are in line with
the Basic Law and other laws of the SAR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
