<DOCNO> XIE19970627.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Helping Handicapped People to Escape Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government helped
600,000 handicapped people solve their food and clothing problems
in 1996, Deng Pufang, chairman of the board of the China Welfare
Fund for the Handicapped, told the 13th meeting of the Board of
Directors, in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
last year, Deng said, China gave 200 million yuan (about 24
million US dollars) in issuing loans and carrying out
poverty-relief activities to help the handicapped in 528
counties. 250,000 cataract sufferers had surgery and 13,000 deaf
children got training. Up to now, the state has provided 530,000
special instruments for handicapped people's daily use, and set up
more than 100 schools to provide special education. In addition,
About 24 million handicapped people in iodine-deficient areas have
been provided with iodized oil, and 93 percent of the cities and
counties, and 72 percent of towns and townships have formulated
regulations on aiding the handicapped and have begun issuing
national welfare certificates to the handicapped.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1995 period, China set up a special fund for
rehabilitation and poverty-relief work among the handicapped and
helped 250,000 handicapped people who were able to work escape the
poverty, according to Deng.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the work of aiding the handicapped has entered a
stage of sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The fund received more than 25 million yuan (three million US
dollars) in overseas donation last year and spent more than 21
million on rehabilitation, education, comprehensive services, and
the cultural and sports activities for the handicapped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
