<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Laws to Be Enforced in Hong Kong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said the Law on China's Territorial Waters and Adjoining
Areas, which is important for national sovereignty over
territorial waters and adjoining areas, should also be added to
the Annex 3 of the Basic Law of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The State Council issued the Announcement of the PRC government
on the Border Line of Chinese Territorial Waters on May 15,
1996. As part of the Law on Territorial Waters and Adjoining Areas
the announcement should be included when the HKSAR makes laws to
implement the law.
</P>
<P>
From July 1, China will begin providing privileges and immunity
to the foreign consular officials and staff members. The People's
Liberation Army troops to be stationed in the HKSAR will enter
Hong Kong at zero hour of July 1.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the Regulations on Consular Privileges and Immunity
in the PRC and the Garrison Law of the PLA Troops Stationed in the
HKSAR, which are necessary for the central government's
administration of HKSAR's foreign and defence affairs, should be
added to Annex 3 of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee of the NPC approved the "Explanation of
Some Problems on Implementing the Nationality Law of the PRC in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region", as part of the
Nationality Law, which should be included if the HKSAR passes new
laws to implement the law, Cao explained.
</P>
<P>
Cao said that, according to Article 18 of the Basic Law of the
HKSAR, "The national laws shall not be applied in the HKSAR except
for those listed in Annex 3 to this Law. The laws listed therein
shall be applied locally in legislation of the Region."
</P>
<P>
"The Standing Committee of the National People's Congress may
add to or delete from the list of laws in Annex 3 after consulting
its Committee for the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region and the Regional government. Laws listed in
Annex 3 to this Law shall be confined to those relating to defence
and foreign affairs and to matters outside the limits of the
autonomy of the Region as specified by this Law."
</P>
<P>
Cao said, according to relevant parts of Article 18, the NPC
Standing Committee will also consult its Committee for the Basic
Law of the HKSAR and the HKSAR government for their opinions on
the draft decision before it is approved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
