<HEADLINE> Air Fares in China to Be Same For Locals and Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- One ticket price will be set for
both overseas and domestic air passengers in China as of July 1.
</P>
<P>
When foreigners purchase tickets on Chinese domestic flights
next month, including the domestic section of international air
routes, they will not pay higher fees, according to a circular
issued by the State Planning Commission and the Civil Aviation
Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
The effort is a move to promote the domestic aviation business,
get involve in international ticketing, maintain the image of
China's reforms and opening-up, and show a more united policy of
the central government towards Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
