<HEADLINE> Two Japanese Get Life Sentence for Drug Possession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A Manila court today meted out life
sentence to two Japanese nationals who were arrested three years
ago for carrying marijuana.
</P>
<P>
The sentence was handed down on Akira Kiyaki and Tomohiza
Kimura, both residents of Makati City, Metro Manila, by the Makati
Regional Trial Court which found them guilty of illegal possession
of prohibited drugs.
</P>
<P>
The court also ordered the two Japanese to pay a fine of
500,000 (19,000 U.S. dollars) each, according to the Philippine
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The two Japanese were arrested in June 1994 along a highway in
Makati City by agents of the Narcotics Command who found 40.6
kilos of dried marijuana bricks inside their car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
