<HEADLINE> Books on Hong Kong's Return Becoming Popular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To cater to the growing interest, stores attached to major
publishers have opened special counters for such publications.
</P>
<P>
A clerk of a store under the Cosmos Book Ltd. said that the
daily sale of books on the subject to the motherland averages
several hundred copies.
</P>
<P>
Miss Wong, who bought books in a store of the Commercial Press
(HK) Ltd., said she and her colleagues are all interested in books
on the subject, since they all want to know what situation they
will face in future.
</P>
<P>
The Joint Publishing (HK) Company has published a series of
books on the subject, all of which have become best-sellers,
according to a company spokesman.
