<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 27 (Xinhua)-- Israel has given a go-ahead for
the construction of Sheikh Zayed City, a 15,000 apartment
project for Palestinians donated by the United Arab Emirates
(UAE) president in Jerusalem, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
