<HEADLINE> Business Community Predicts Bright Future for HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Noted Hong Kong business leaders
today predicted a bright future for Hong Kong as it is the world's
gateway to China, and vice versa.
</P>
<P>
Michael Sze, executive director of the HK Trade Development
Council, Paul Chow, chief executive of the HSBC Asset Management
HK Ltd, Norman Yuen, deputy chief executive of the Hong Kong
Telecom, and Victor Chu, chairman of Far Eastern Holding Ltd.,
were among those present at today's briefing.
</P>
