After briefing the press on the outstanding achievements Hong
Kong has scored over the past few years, the management executives
held that Hong Kong's status as an international financial, trade,
shipping, information center will not change but be further
enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will witness a closer tie with the rest of China
after its return to China under the guidance of the "one country,
two system" principle, said Victor Chu.
</P>
<P>
Paul Chow acknowledged that Hong Kong, which has a complete
banking and financial system, is a major market for banking
consortiums in the Asia-Pacific area. It is also an important
arena for Hong Kong banking business to provide fund raising
service for the interior areas, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong boasts the world's most complete and developed
telecommunication network, which will give an impetus to the
economic progress in the interior areas, said Norman Yuen.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the businessmen noted, Hong Kong will be an
important thoroughfare for the interior areas to link with the
international market. 
