<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Visiting Russian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting with Russian Prime Minister Victor Chernomyrdin here
today, said that the development of the strategic partnership
between China and Russia will most certainly bring a good
Sino-Russian relationship into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"In next century, our two countries will enjoy better
relations," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Sino-Russian ties have seen big growth in recent
years and that the two countries have signed four joint
communiques that determined the ways and means for Sino-Russian
long-term cooperation for the next century.
</P>
<P>
Principles have been established for increasing bilateral ties
and strengthening cooperation in various fields, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Sino-Russian relations will grow
steadily and healthily just as long as the two sides stick to the
spirit of equality, mutual trust, good neighborliness, and
cooperation for mutual benefit and joint development.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin told Jiang that promoting Russia-China ties is a
priority in Russian foreign relations and that there are many
possibilities for cooperation. The two sides are now cooperating
effectively in the economy and in trade, he said, adding that he
hopes there will be more and better cooperation projects between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the regular meetings between the two prime
ministers are very good, something that could make for overall
planning in pushing forward bilateral collaboration, including
some large projects of major strategic importance.
</P>
<P>
This mechanism has proven effective and has shown vitality
since it began, Jiang continued. New progress will be made, he
said, as long as the two sides start from a strategic point of
view and continue to consult each other in a practical way.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin congratulated China on the return of Hong Kong,
calling it a major event in the 20th century and said that Russia
believes that Hong Kong's prospects will be even better.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that all Chinese are inspired by the return of Hong
Kong, and that this is an important step in China's reunification
of the motherland in accordance with the "one country, two
systems" concept presented by Deng Xiaoping, and that this step
has far-reaching historical significance.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he believes that after the handover, Hong Kong will
be even more prosperous and will continue to make a distinct
contribution to the development of the Asia-Pacific region and the
world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also told Chernomyrdin that China expects President Boris
Yeltsin to visit China at his convenience.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
