<HEADLINE> CPPCC Standing Committee Holds Meeting in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Committee, China's top political advisory body, held
its 21st session today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided over by Li Ruihuan, a Standing
Committee member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China and chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee. The three-day session will concentrate on the study of
Deng Xiaoping's theory on people's political consultative system.
</P>
<P>
At the open meeting, Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the CPPCC
National Committee, said that the meeting will also summarize the
committee's performance over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
The current committee has concentrated on learning about and
reflecting the public will, expanding ties with "patriotic
figures" at home and abroad by increasing exchanges with CPPCC
members in Hong Kong and Macao, and promoting the cause of
peaceful reunification of the motherland, according to Ye.
</P>
<P>
The session will also discuss preparation for the CPPCC
election next year. 
</P>
