<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Discusses Ending of Preparatory Committee for HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature began
deliberations today on ending the National People's Congress's
Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
According to the legislature's draft, the Preparatory Committee
has met its goal of preparing to establish the HKSAR according to
the HKSAR Basic Law and decisions of the NPC and its standing
committee, after it was established in January, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee is expected to approve the proposal
on ending the Preparatory Committee, which held its ninth session
on May 22, where it was decided that the preparatory committee had
basically completed the job of preparing to establish the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The final plenum of the Preparatory Committee is scheduled for
July 11, where it will announce the end of the committee.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee said that it formed the Selection
Committee for the First Government of the Hong Kong SAR, composed
of 400 permanent Hong Kong residents. It also presided over
meetings of the Selection Committee to choose candidates for the
first Chief Executive and members of the Provisional Legislative
Council.
</P>
<P>
It devised a method for forming the first Legislative Council
of the Hong Kong SAR and studied major economic issues concerning
the handover of power and smooth transition of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It also made suggestions on the right of abode and nationality
of Hong Kong residents, added and deleted laws to and from the
national laws of Hong Kong for the SAR, and submitted them to the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress for review.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
