<HEADLINE> Lusaka Businessmen Sentenced for Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Lusaka businessmen were found
guilty and sentenced by the Lusaka Magistrate Court today for
trafficking more than 20 kilograms of cannabis.
</P>
<P>
The two, Alarm Sikaonga and Lucas Sagile, were arrested by the
police at a road block on a van they were traveling on after a
policeman searched the vehicle and found cannabis concealed in
two bags on April 10 this year.
</P>
<P>
In mitigation, the two criminals pleaded for forgiveness and
promised never to trafficking such drugs again.
</P>
<P>
The magistrate, Betty Musongko, gave the two a suspended
sentence of two years as they were first offenders and had shown
willingness and a repentance never to commit the crime again.
</P>
<P>
She, however, warned that while the economic problems are
affecting everyone, it is not an excuse to get involved in
criminal activities and then end up being imprisoned. 
</P>
