<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Securities Watchdog Confident in HK Financial Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will continue to
prosper and maintain its status as an international financial
center after it becomes a special administrative region of China
on July 1, Anthony Neoh, chairman of the HK Securities &AMP; Futures
Commission, said here today.
</P>
<P>
With only four days to go before the Hong Kong's return to
China, Neoh made a detailed analysis of the strength, advantages
and new opportunities for Hong Kong's financial market, in a
speech titled "Building up Confidence and Keeping Abreast of the
Time".
</P>
<P>
"The ultimate goal of market supervision is to build up
confidence," he said. "A market cannot thrive if the investors do
not have much faith in it."
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the Hang Seng Index has been
rising rapidly, he added, and both the overall market value and
the transaction volume of stocks have reached a new height.
</P>
<P>
"This has indicated the strong confidence in the market," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The overall market value of the securities on the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange, which has more than 620 listed companies, has now
approached 600 billion US dollars, and the transaction volume for
the first four months this year totaled 102 billion US dollars,
more than half of the overall transaction volume of 183 billion US
dollars for 1996.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong stock market is the world's eighth largest, and
the number two in Asia next to Tokyo," said Neoh. "It is a major
fund-raising channel for enterprises in China's interior areas."
</P>
<P>
Since the first enterprise from China's interior was listed in
Hong Kong in 1993, he noted, there have been 32 H shares at
present -- shares for companies from China's interior areas -- on
the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, which have raised a total capital of
6.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local stock market would suspended business during the first
three days of the next week, he noted, and the July 1 decision by
the US Federal Reserve Board on the change of interest rate could
have some impact on the market.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, he said, "We have made necessary preparations to
deal with any possible risks."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hong Kong's markets for futures and funds have also
been developing steadily, he added.
</P>
<P>
At present, some 200 fund companies are doing business in Hong
Kong, and there are over 1,300 government-recognized funds with
total assets worth nearly 100 billion US dollars in the market.
Hong Kong has become the second largest fund management center in
Asia.
</P>
<P>
"To preserve Hong Kong's current advantages, our commission
will work to maintain a fair, effective and transparent market,
and strive to establish a supervisory system that is compatible
with the international standards," said Neoh, who became the
chairman in early 1995.
</P>
<P>
The commission will also increase its cooperation with China's
interior areas in the aspect of market supervision, and encourage
the participation of international institutions in the Hong Kong
market, he added.
</P>
<P>
Describing the "China factor" as Hong Kong's "unique and
incomparable advantage", he said the listing of enterprises from
the interior area in Hong Kong was just the beginning, and that
more interior state-owned enterprise will come here to raise fund
as a result of the rapid growth of economy and the increasing
needs for capital.
</P>
<P>
"This has been and will continue to be a powerful impetus for
Hong Kong to establish itself as the center of capitalization in
the Asia-Pacific region," he said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the H shares, there are now also scores of "red
chips", stocks of companies funded by China's interior areas that
are registered and operating in Hong Kong, on the Hong Kong Stock
Market. They account for six to seven percent of the total market
value of all listed stocks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
