<HEADLINE> NPC 26th Meeting in Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Eighth National People's Congress, China's top legislature, today
approved the establishment of a special work committee for the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
In its 26th session which opened here today, the Standing
Committee selected 12 members for the new committee, half of whom
are from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The new committee will assume its responsibilities on July 1.
</P>
<P>
This session, which is to last seven days, will debate on a
motion to increase the number of national laws to be applied in
future HKSAR from present six to ten.
</P>
<P>
The laws to be added include those concerning national defense
and foreign affairs, such as the national flag law, that were
promulgated after the Basic law was worked out.
</P>
<P>
The session is expected to approve a draft resolution to end
the work by the Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR. Also on the
agenda are several draft laws for deliberation, including laws on
highways and animal quarantine.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance will submit its 1996 financial
accounting of central revenue and expenditure for approval by the
session. 
</P>
