<HEADLINE> Dhaka Supports Palestinian People for Setting up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina today reiterated her country's total support to the
Palestinian people in their just struggle for establishing a
separate and independent homeland with Jerusalem as their capital.
</P>
<P>
In her message on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of the
illegal occupation of Jerusalem city, Prime Minister Hasina
condemned the continuation of the occupation of the holy city by
Israel since June 1967.
</P>
<P>
She said that "we condemns this annexation of the holy city by
Israel and the illegal measures and practices such as confiscation
of land property, establishment of Jewish settlements, demolition
of Palestinian homes, profanation of Islamic and Christian holy
places."
</P>
<P>
"Israel is obstructing the freedom of worship, executing
excavation works, opened the tunnels, withdrawn the documents of
identity from the Palestinian inhabitants of Jerusalem," said
Hasina.
</P>
<P>
She noted that Jerusalem city has been isolated from Arab
environment and economic blockade has also been imposed by the
occupied Israeli authorities.
</P>
<P>
"Bangladesh supports a just, durable and comprehensive solution
to the Middle East problem," said the prime minister, who also
called upon the international community to extend all necessary
support and assistance to the Palestinian people.  
