<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Ready For ECOWAS Delegation Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, June 27 (Xinhua) - The Secretary-General of the
military junta in Sierra Leone, Colonel Abdul Sesay said Friday
that the government is ready for visit from its neighboring
states.
</P>
<P>
He said his government "welcome the coming visit of a four-man
delegation from ECOWAS as well as the OAU secretariat", which
will give them the "opportunity to see things for themselves on
the ground".
</P>
<P>
