will give them the opportunity to explain that their aim was not
the power, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sesay, who was giving the junta's initial reaction to the
foreign ministers meeting held in neighboring Guinea, said "we
have always stressed that we would not stay in power endlessly
but would work for the restoration of democracy in the shortest
period".
</P>
<P>
He said in the telephone interview with Xinhua, that they were
anxious to consolidate the peace and nothing should now disrupt
that.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the junta has appointed 17 supervisors to oversee
the administration of government departments.
</P>
<P>
These appointees are holding the functions on a temporary
basis until a broadbased government is formed, Sesay said.
