<HEADLINE> Global Forum for Health Research Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- "Global Forum for Health Research"
was launched here today, providing a platform for furthering
dialogues and creating new partnerships among all those involved
in health research in both public and private sectors.
</P>
<P>
The forum, a non-governmental organization, was launched at a
meeting hosted by the World Health Organization (WHO). It was
attended by some 150 representatives of governments and
international organizations including the World Bank, the Swiss
Agency for Development and Cooperation, non-governmental women's
organizations, research institutions and private pharmaceutical
companies.
</P>
<P>
The forum will discuss allocations for research of the most
debilitating global health problems, a WHO press release said.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the forum are expected to discuss support for
concerted research efforts focused on the health needs of poor
societies.
</P>
<P>
Adetokunbo O. Lucas of Nigeria, former director of the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP)/World Bank/WHO Special Program
for Research and Training in Tropical Diseases, was nominated as
the forum's first chairman.
</P>
<P>
Within one year, the forum's six working groups will emphasize
research and training in health policy, rational investments in
health research, anti-violence activities, and a public/private
sector alliance for malaria research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
