<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
weaker today, weighed by a hike in Canadian short term interest
rates overnight which sparked selling of the local unit.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished in Sydney at 74.90 US cents,
down from 75.10 at the previous session close.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) board meets on Tuesday
while the Federal Reserve holds its policy making meeting on
Tuesday and Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Overnight, the Australian dollar dipped to a low of 74.85 US
cents after the surprise move by the Bank of Canada to lift the
bank rate by 25 basis points to 3.5 percent and the target
overnight call range to 3.0 percent to 3.5 percent, from 2.75
percent to 3.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
While many market participants think the Reserve Bank could
ease next week, others believe any rate cut might be delayed until
after the US Federal Reserve conclude its policy meeting.
</P>
<P>
The risk is that the Fed might lift US interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 85.43 yen, up from 85.46 , and at
1.2922 marks from 1.2942.  
</P>
