<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Indonesian Parliament Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), said that
the NPC values its exchanges with the Indonesian House, and is
willing to expand its exchanges and cooperation with it.
</P>
<P>
Qiao made the remark here this afternoon while meeting with a
delegation from the Indonesian House of Representatives, led by
its Deputy Speaker Soetedjo.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qiao recalled his visit to Indonesia in
July, 1993, saying that he received a warm reception given by
Indonesian House colleagues and people of various circles, and had
good talks with Indonesian President Suharto and Parliament
leaders.
</P>
<P>
Qiao noted that China and Indonesia are friendly neighbors, and
the two peoples enjoy a long history of exchanges.
</P>
<P>
In the past over six years since the restoration of
Sino-Indonesian diplomatic ties, Qiao said, their bilateral
relations have developed well with frequent high-level exchanges.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, he continued, the two countries have
made remarkable achievements in political, economic and cultural
exchanges. "these years have seen rapid growth in economic and
trade relations between the two countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also mentioned progress in economic and technological
cooperation, adding that the two countries have steadily
strengthened their cooperation in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the relations between the two parliaments are an
important component in bilateral ties, Qiao pointed out that to
further strengthen friendly exchanges between the two parliaments
can not only enhance friendship between the two peoples, but is
also conducive to the overall development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
he said that China and the ASEAN (Association for Southeast
Asian Nations) countries including Indonesia enjoy very good
relations. he stressed that to accept Cambodia, the Laos and
Myanmar soon as its new members is an important step in the
process of ASEAN's progress.
</P>
<P>
"China hopes to see a prosperous, stable and vigorous Southeast
Asia, and is willing to further strengthen cooperation with
Indonesia and all other ASEAN countries, and join them in working
for peace and development in the region and the world at large,"
Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
Soetedjo expressed his congratulations on Hong Kong's return to
its motherland and emphasized that his country supports the great
cause of China's peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that Hong Kong will return to the motherland soon,
and China will implement the policies of "one country, two
systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong, and a high-degree
of autonomy in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said he is convinced that a smooth transfer of the political
power of Hong Kong will be realized. He reiterated China's
determination to guarantee Hong Kong's long-term prosperity and
stability.
</P>
<P>
Soetedjo said that the delegation's current visit here is aimed
at further deepening mutual understanding, trust and friendship.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed Indonesian House Speaker Wahono's greetings to
Qiao, who, in return, asked Soetedjo to convey his regards to
Wahono.  
</P>
