<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 53 in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Officials in the Ministry of
Public Health of Cameroun revealed here today that Cholera has
killed 53 and infected about 1000 people in the country in the
past two months.
</P>
<P>
Water has been noted as one of the main sources of cholera
epidemic which have been reported in the far north, central,
western and littoral provinces.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic situation this year has necessitated some urgent
measures by the Ministry of Public Health to check the spread of
the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
Some of the provincial delegations of Public Health are
undergoing a sensitization on the fight against the epidemic
through the radio and private press.
</P>
<P>
The ministry warned the whole country to keep an eye on their
drinking water and to clean their food and fruits properly before
eating.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Ministry of Public Health recorded 5,893 cholera
cases in three northern provinces where water remains a scarcity.
</P>
</TEXT>
