<HEADLINE> Djibril Re-elected as Cameroun's National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Yeguie Djibril was re-elected the
speaker of the National Assembly of Cameroun during a plenary
session of the assembly which lasted all night Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He scored a total of 158 votes out of 171.
</P>
<P>
Djibril, born in 1940, was elected the parliamentarian in the
National Assembly between 1972 and 1988.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, he was re-elected the parliamentarian and at the same
time became the speaker of the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Cameroun's new National Assembly was inaugurated on June 17,
1997. The first plenary session is now undergoing and the mandate
of 171 parliamentarians elected out of 173 were validated during
the session. 
</P>
