<HEADLINE> New Era of Cooperation Between HK with Other Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A leading Chinese expert said here
today that the cooperation between Hong Kong and other parts of
China, especially southern areas, will play an important role in
maintaining the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong
after it returns to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Fu Chonglan, director of the Urban Development and Environment
Research Center of the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, said
Hong Kong and its neighboring areas will enter a more prosperous
era after July 1, as a result of their further cooperation in a
wide range of sectors.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, as an international center of finance, trade,
shipping, tourism, and information, will face stronger competition
in the world market, Fu said, and he foresees more advantageous
exchanges between Hong Kong and the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The two-way cooperation in trade and economics, the sciences,
technology, and social welfare programs will continue to develop,
and the central-western area of China will become an investment
hot spot for Hong Kong businessmen, according to Fu.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that technological and agricultural involvement
between Hong Kong and the inland areas will help increase their
competitiveness in farming and hi-tech development in the domestic
and international markets.
</P>
<P>
Fu stresses importance of paying attention to environmental
protection and ecological problems in Hong Kong and its
surrounding areas, while they strengthen cooperations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
