difficulty of making the two ends of electoral promises and
commitment to Europe meet. Economic projections said that
France's budget deficit this year would stand around 3.7 percent
of its gross domestic product, higher than the 3 percent ceiling
set by its 1997 budget law in accordance with the Maastricht
treaty criteria for joining the euro.
</P>
<P>
-- The United States Supreme Court ruled Thursday that the
Communication Decency Act, a federal law banning Internet messages
judged as "indecent," is unconstitutional. Many users of the
Internet have complained that the law would open the door to an
unacceptable form of censorship.
</P>
