</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister Lionel Jospin Thursday asked his cabinet
ministers to prepare the 1998 budget law by giving "absolute
priority to the fight for employment and social justice" while
"all respecting the European commitments for entering the economic
and monetary union on the deadline set by the (Maastricht) treaty."
</P>
<P>
-- Paris remains a hub of drug-trafficking and drug-abuse of
France despite strong competition from Marseille known for its
"French Connection" in the 1970s, said specialists attending a
conference of European Cities Against Drug (ECAD) Thursday.
</P>
