<HEADLINE> Disarmament Conference Approves New Coordinator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Conference on Disarmament (CD)
approved Thursday the appointment of John Campbell of Australia as
a "Special Coordinator" on the issue of landmines.
</P>
<P>
But the conference still has not adopted a program of work for
this year although the appointment ended in part a deadlock over
what CD should do in this year's session.
</P>
<P>
The appointment, made at a plenary of the second part of the CD
1997 session, followed a consensus among CD members that a special
coordinator should be chosen.
</P>
<P>
A further plenary was set for Friday following requests for
decisions on several other proposed appointments of ad hoc committees
and special coordinators.
</P>
<P>
Campbell, ambassador and permanent representative of Australia
to CD, will explore possibilities for beginning negotiations on an
international ban on anti-personnel landmines.
</P>
<P>
He is requested to consult with member delegations and report
to the conference on how to proceed on the topic of landmine
negotiations when it resumes work in August. 
</P>
