<HEADLINE> Cameroun Calls for Fight Against Drug Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Cameroun's Minister of Public
Health has called for the entire society to make concerted effort
to fight against drug abuse, local radio reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Charle Etoundi, the Minister of Public Health of Cameroun,
made the speech in Yaounde Thursday as Camerounians joined the
international community to celebrate the 10th International Day
Against Drug Abuse.
</P>
<P>
The day is observed this year under the theme: Mobilizing the
Civil Society in the Fight Against Drug Abuse.
</P>
<P>
Etoundi said drug abuse was first and foremost a personal
tragedy which made the individual run into crime, loss of job,
house and health.
</P>
<P>
The minister called on parents in particular and the public in
general to help guard the youth against drug abuse. 
</P>
