<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by another 15.43 points to close at
1,974.37 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 176.68 million units,
valued at 383.52 million Singapore dollars (about 268.2 million US
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 190 to 117, while 317
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Newly listed Tianjin Zhiyao was the most actively traded stock
as it registered a turnover of 72.71 million units. It was
followed by Van der Horst which had 7.49 million shares traded.
The Hong Kong Land was next with 5.83 million of its shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 24.5 Singapore
dollars. NBT increased by 40 cents to end at 21.3 Singapore
dollars, while the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign and
Samanda Holdings picked up by 30 cents each to close at 28.6 and
12.9 Singapore dollar respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Roth M was the biggest loser as it declined by
1.3 dollars to end at 14 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank
of Singapore (DBS) Foreign fell by 80 cents to close at 17.7
Singapore dollars, while local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage
(C&AMP;C) and GE Life finished 50 cents lower at 14.4 and 16 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
