<HEADLINE> Hainan Encourages Social Forces to Run Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A growing number of enterprises,
social organizations and individuals in south China's Hainan
Province have become school administrators.
</P>
<P>
The province has 174 non-government-owned kindergartens, and
more than 20 middle schools and 50-plus vocational schools run by
groups not affiliated with the state.
</P>
<P>
Society's participation in educational administration has
satisfied a variety of the public's demands for quality education,
officials here say.
</P>
<P>
Local educational departments are encouraging
non-government-owned schools to exchange classroom experiences and
management skills, in a move to promote the healthy development of
the schools. 
