<HEADLINE> Suspected Gunmen Shot Dead in Lusaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Zambian policemen have shot dead
two suspected, wounded one and captured four others in a heavy
gunfire exchange with eight gunmen in the Zambian capital.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place in Lusaka's Chawama township Thursday
when the gunmen raided the house of a businessman, according to
police public relations officer Standwell Lungu.
</P>
<P>
While confirming the incident, Lungu said that the slain were
among 53 prisoners released by the High Court last year. The due
aged 22 to 25 are on the wanted list for a series of aggravated
robberies in the capital.
</P>
<P>
A manhunt has been launched for the lone suspect who is on the
run, according to the police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
There have been reports about robberies and gunfire exchanges
between policemen and bandits in the Zambian capital and some
other cities. However, observers are of the view that the
incidents have not yet constituted grave threat to social order.
</P>
