<DOCNO> XIE19970627.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 07:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Launches Air Attack at Hezbollah in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli helicopters carried
out an air raid at a guerrilla base of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah,
or Party of God, in south Lebanon Thursday night, and Hezbollah
sources confirmed this morning that one guerrilla was injured in
the strike.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli helicopters launched the offensive at 11:00
p.m. local time (08:00 GMT) and fired five air-to-surface missiles
at the target on the outskirts of Nabaa Al-Taseh in Iglim
Al-Toffah, or Province of Apple, a heights opposite the so-called
"security zone" self-carved by Israel in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Senior security sources in Hezbollah said that Hassan Farah, a
Hezbollah guerrilla, was injured when the military jeep he was
driving in the area was hit by the helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The air raid was accompanied by bombardment of Israeli
artillery at Loueizeh, Ogmatah, and Sejoud in Iglim Al-Toffah,
some 65 kilometers southeast of Beirut, which is often used by
Hezbollah's Muslim fighters as a springboard to launch attacks on
the buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
Police sources in south Lebanon said that Israeli artillery
resumed the shelling this morning at Iglim Al-Toffah and fired a
dozen of 120m and 150m heavy shells.
</P>
<P>
However, local military observers noted that Thursday night's
air raid, the 41st since this year, did not go beyond a limit of
daily exchange of fire between the Lebanese resistance fighters
and the Israeli occupation forces on the last active battlefront
of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone"
in 1985 ostensibly to protect northern Israel from cross-border
attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
