<HEADLINE> South China City Attracts More Investment From Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, capital of south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has so far set up 423 Hong
Kong-funded enterprises, involving more than 512 million US
dollars of Hong Kong financing.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 percent of overseas-funded enterprises in Nanning are
joint efforts of Hong Kong business people.
</P>
<P>
Nanning has become one of the leading cities in China in terms
of overseas investment, with more than 60 percent of such funding
coming from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Nanning has implemented the country's coastal opening-up
policies for five years, and has been issuing a series of
preferential policies to attract overseas investment. 
