<HEADLINE> Brazil Routs Peru 7-0 to Reach Copa America Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LA PAZ, June 26 (Xinhua) -- World champion Brazil mercilessly
rolled over Peru 7-0 Thursday in Santa Cruz, Bolivia, reaching
the final of the Copa America soccer championship.
</P>
<P>
The Brazlians were ahead after just two minutes and had taken a
4-0 lead by halftime in the most lopsided game of the championship.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Leonardo scored two goals while World Cup hero
Romario scored twice before limping off injured in the 70th minute
after pulling a muscle.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's other goals came from Denilson, Flavio Conceicao and
Djalminha.
</P>
<P>
Peru, midway in the South American World Cup qualifying
tournament, sent a second-string team to South America's biggest
soccer event.
</P>
<P>
Brazil faces a tough task in Sunday's final its plays host
Bolivia in La Paz, at 3,600 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a clash of giants," said Brazil coach Mario Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians jumped ahead through Denilson's goal in the
second minute. Flavio Conceicao scored the second goal with a
powerful 30-meter blast in the 28th minute and Romaria put it 3-0
eight minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the first half's injury time, Leonardo headed home a perfect
cross from Cafu.
</P>
<P>
Romario and Leonardo helped themselves to a second goal each in
the first 15 minutes after halftime.
</P>
<P>
Djalminha rounded off the tally with eight minutes from time.
</P>
</TEXT>
