<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Drug Abuse "Rising Rapidly" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Drug abuse was rapidly on
the rise in South Africa and children as young as nine were using
drugs, the South African Narcotics Bureau said in a statement
issued here today.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's official Vince Crous said in the first four
months of this year police confiscated two tons of dagga in
Pretoria, compared with three kilogram in the some period last
year.
</P>
<P>
He attributed this increase to the opening up of international
markets and poor socio-economic conditions.
</P>
<P>
South Africans, he stressed, were the biggest abusers of
Mandrax in the world.
</P>
<P>
Crous told a public briefing that up to 85 percent of all
South African teenagers experimented with drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
