<HEADLINE> Hainan Farmers Create Associations to Meet Challenges of Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in China's southernmost
Hainan Province have set up 728 agricultural-oriented
organizations to lower production costs and make themselves more
competitive in a market economy.
</P>
<P>
The groups are registered in local commercial and industrial
administration departments.
</P>
<P>
"This shows that Hainan has made great progress in establishing
a social service system for farming in the countryside," according
to local authorities.
</P>
<P>
The organizations deal with agricultural issues related to
technology services, sales of agricultural products and livestock,
and transportation and processing of farm products.
</P>
<P>
The Chicken-Raising Association, set up by famers in Shangyong
Township in the city of Qionghai, sells about 60 percent of the
chickens raised by its members every year, and gives training
programs on production technology. 
