<HEADLINE> China to Set up Wine Museum in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A museum dedicated to the history
and production of yellow rice wine will be built in the birthplace
of the drink, Shaoxing City, in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The 20-million-yuan museum will provide visitors with a broad
range of information about the wine's background, production
technology, the raw materials used to make it, and its nutritional
value.
</P>
<P>
The museum, which covers 20 hectares, will also display several
historical items representing wine production and culture,
including wine containers and replicas of different styles of
wineries.
</P>
<P>
A number of wine-making workshops will be held to give tourists
a chance to practice their skills.
</P>
<P>
Yellow rice wine has a history of 2,500 years. 
</P>
