<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Warship Visits Japan for First Time in 103 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A Russian warship arrived at Tokyo
port this morning for a four-day stay in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The 7,600-ton Admiral Vinogradov, a destroyer belonging to the
Pacific Fleet of the Russian Navy, became the first Russian
warship to pay a port call to Japan in 103 years.
</P>
<P>
The last visit to Japan by a Russian warship was in 1894, when
a vessel came to Tokyo for a ceremony in honor of Emperor Meiji's
25th wedding anniversary, said the Japanese Defense Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Russian warship's first postwar visit was arranged in April
1996, when defense chiefs of Japan and Russian agreed in Moscow to
send war vessels to each other's country for goodwill visits.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Maritime Self-Defense Force sent its vessel Kurama to
Vladivostok in July last year, to join an event marking the
Russian Navy's 300th anniversary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
