<HEADLINE> HK to Improve Medical Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will continue to
improve its medical service after its return to China on July 1,
said Dr. E K Yeoh, Chief Executive of the Hospital Authority.
</P>
<P>
To improve health care for Hong Kong residents, the Hospital
Authority has formulated a number of specific measures, including
the perfection of a wide-range and efficient medical care system,
planning and improving clinical services; enhancement of the role
of communities by letting them become involved in the
policy-making process to improve the efficiency of medical
services; the improvement and development of the existing medical
service structure; and improvement of infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1990, the Hospital Authority is an independent
government department that takes charge of supervising and
administrating Hong Kong's government-run hospitals. The authority
administers 41 hospitals and 48 special clinics.  
