<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Soldiers Detained for Passing Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Eight Sri Lankan Muslim soldiers
have been detained by military authorities for allegedly supplying
information to the Tamil rebels, according to military sources
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the initial arrest was of one Muslim soldier
on the Jaffna Peninsula, who had earlier been attached to the
intelligence wing of the Tamil rebels.
</P>
