<HEADLINE> hkhk - Hong Kong-related Data (15): Preliminary Working Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Preliminary Working
Committee (PWC) of the Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) is an institution
established in accordance with a decision made in July 1993 at the
Second Session of the Eighth National People's Congress Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Its responsibility was to make preparatory work for China's
resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong in 1997 and
for Hong Kong's smooth transition prior to the establishment of
the Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The committee was composed of personages of various social
circles and specialists in the inland areas and Hong Kong, with
those from Hong Kong accounting for no less than 50 percent. It
was to stop functioning when the Preparatory Committee was set up.
</P>
<P>
Under the PWC were five sub-groups dealing respectively with
political affairs, legal affairs, the economy, culture, and social
and public security.
</P>
<P>
They offered specific suggestions on the formation of the HKSAR
and on Hong Kong's smooth transition, and did a great deal of work
for the establishment and operation of the Preparatory Committee
in 1996 and China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
