<HEADLINE> Firm Issues 100 Million A-Shares for Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou Power Enterprise
(Holdings) Co Ltd (GZPEHCL) will be listed on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange on June 27 with an offer of 100 million A-shares,
according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The issuance is expected to raise 787 million yuan for the
remaining construction of the Guangzhou Pearl River Power Plant's
second-phase project and for the construction of its third-phase
project, said Yang Dandi, general manager of the company.
</P>
<P>
The funds to be raised will also be applied to the construction
of the Guangzhou Panyu Power Plant.
</P>
<P>
"Floating stocks in Shanghai are to integrate the financial
advantages of both Guangzhou and Shanghai," said the general
manager. "And such a step will pave the way for the company's
future development on a higher level to meet the city's demand for
electricity supply."
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's economy is growing at an estimated rate of 12
percent on a year-on-year basis, intensifying the need for
electricity supply and ensuring rosy prospects for the development
of the company, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The second-phase project of the Guangzhou Pearl River Power
Plant is scheduled to go into operation late this year and the
third-phase project is scheduled to be completed in the early 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
When all the projects are completed, the power plant will boast
a capacity of 2.4 million kilowatts, able to generate electricity
of 12 billion kilowatt hours annually.
</P>
<P>
GZPEHCL, the city's largest base generating power and a prime
power supplier, holds 50 percent of Guangzhou Pearl River Power Co
Ltd's stocks and 65 percent of Guangzhou Dongfang Power Co Ltd's
stocks.
</P>
<P>
The company also boasts seven solely owned subordinates.
</P>
