<HEADLINE> World Bank Loan Aids China's Essential Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank is providing 830
million US dollars in loans for the two infrastructure projects in
China, according to today's "China Daily."
</P>
<P>
The bank's board approved a 430 million US dollars loan to the
Xiaolangdi Multipurpose Project Second Stage and another 400
million US dollars lending program to the Shanghai Waigaoqiao
Thermal Power Project.
</P>
<P>
The gigantic Xiaolangdi project was designed to provide flood
protection for 103 million people in rural areas, cities and major
industrial areas along the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
The newly approved credit from the bank will be used for the
construction of a dam and hydroelectric power plant of the river
and further the government's work in water resources schemes.
</P>
<P>
While the Xiaolangdi project will benefit mainly rural
development, the Waigaoqiao project is designed to break the power
bottleneck for Shanghai, China's most important industrial city.
</P>
<P>
The 1.9 billion thermal power project will provide the Shanghai
Municipal Electric Power Co. with two large coal-fired super
critical thermal units for its Waigaoqiao plant, equipped with
performance monitoring systems which will minimize coal
consumption and gradually introduce advanced maintenance
techniques, the paper says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
