<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Energetically Against Drug Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan Province
has dealt with 6,245 drug-related cases this year, and arrested a
large number of suspects.
</P>
<P>
The local police have seized 38.12 kg of heroin and broke up
215 gangs involved in drugs. Nearly 140 drug dens have been
destroyed, officials say.
</P>
<P>
The court has pronounced more than 300 people guilty in
connection with drug-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has established 21 rehabilitation
centers for drug addicts.  
</P>
