<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nine Wounded at Election Rally in Albania (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were wounded by gunfire
on Thursday during an election rally of the ruling Democratic
Party in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The shooting broke out when President Sali Berisha began to
address a crowd of several hundred, which included a few of his
supporters, in Lushnje, about 80 kilometers south of the capital
Tirana, says an AFP report.
</P>
<P>
Democratic Party officials immediately blamed the opposition
for the violence.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the gunfire apparently came from both
sides. Berisha had tried in vain to appeal for calm before he left
the city.
</P>
<P>
However, the shooting did not affect his another rally in
Kavaja, a city to the southwest of Tirana, which is a stronghold
of the Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
Tensions have occurred in Albania, especially in the south, as
the Sunday legislative election approaches. The election is
regarded as the last chance to restore peace in this troubled
Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
Protests broke out against Berisha last March when many people
found they had been cheated of the life savings by a failed
get-rich-quick scheme.
</P>
<P>
The Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe has
sent observers to Albania to oversee the elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
