<HEADLINE> European Shares End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- All shares on Europe's major stock
markets closed higher today.
</P>
<P>
British shares ended higher for a third day, as worries over
next week's budget eased and nerves were calmed by a firm early
showing on Wall Street. The FTSE-100 closed at 4,657.9, up 17.9
points.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, shares notched up more records as the blue chip
DAX reached an all-time high close, but profit-taking took the
edge off the market's advance. The DAX-30 index closed at
3,805.29, up 6.78 points. In later screen-based trade the IBIS DAX
index ended at 3,820.16, up 0.64 points.
</P>
<P>
French stocks hit a record high, with the CAC-40 index closing
at 2,893.64, up 26.20 points. 
