<HEADLINE> More Hong Kong Funds Pouring into Suzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 95 Hong Kong-funded
enterprises have been set up in the Suzhou New Area in east
China's Jiangsu Province, with investment totaling 587 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, some 38 percent of the
overseas-funded enterprises and 29 percent of the overseas
investments are from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhou New Area, a State-level new and high-tech
development zone, has become another money-maker for the city
after five years' growth.
</P>
<P>
To date, a total of 280 overseas-funded enterprises have been
set up in the Suzhou New Area, with total financing hitting three
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
With the approaching of Hong Kong's return to the motherland on
July 1, the economic ties between Hong Kong and the Suzhou New
Area have become closer. So far, some 21 Hong Kong-funded
enterprises, each with investment of more than 10 million US
dollars, have been set up in the New Area, including the city's
largest overseas-funded enterprise.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investment into the zone mainly centers on real
estate, tourism, catering and interior decoration, said the
source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
