<HEADLINE> Spain Upsets Croats in European Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain rallied from behind to upset
fancied Croatia 78-71 for the first surprise in the European
basketball championship in Genora on Thursday .
</P>
<P>
The win awarded the hosts a place in the second phase as three
top teams in each group advance further.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania and Greece also went through after notching up their
second victories in tough games against France and Russia
respectively,
</P>
<P>
Croatia finished the first half with a four-point advantage,
but Spain turned the table through naturalized American Mike Smith.
</P>
<P>
Despite the defeat, Croatia was almost certain to go through,
as only the bottom team from each group will be eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Greece started strongly to build up a commanding 39-21 lead
against Russia before Russian Igor Koudelin scored consecutive
three-pointers to narrow the gap to 10 points at the break.
</P>
<P>
Finally, the Greeks struggled to take the game 74-72.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania was once again led by Arturas Karnisovas in the 94-88
win over France. Karnisovas scored 31 points and was backed up by
centre Einikis Gintaras, who scored 27.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, Poland and Bosnia were all facing early exits from the
competition having lost both their opening games. Ukraine were
beaten 81-60 by Germany, Bosnia lost 70-62 to Turkey, while Latvia
went down 79-86 to Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
