<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China New Attraction for Hong Kong Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, the fourth
province-level municipality approved by China's National People's
Congress, has become a new attraction for Hong Kong investors.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has had 1.52 billion US dollars in Hong Kong
investment and has approved 1,061 Hong Kong-funded companies,
which account for half of the overseas-backed companies in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The sectors favored by Hong Kong business people are
transportation, food processing, real estate, textiles, chemical
industry and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the largest transit center for Chongqing's foreign
trade, and is the leading buyer of the city's machinery,
instruments, and medical products.
</P>
<P>
Because of the flourishing trade, Hong Kong companies have a
big share of Chongqing's electronics, printing equipment,
ready-to-wear clothing, toys, and food markets.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the increasingly extensive economic ties,
Chongqing, with its natural resources and labor, and Hong Kong,
with its advantages in international trade, should go farther and
form a reciprocal economic relationship, economists say.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing government has worked out a development strategy
for promoting bilateral trade, aimed at extending the market to
Southeast Asia and South Asia via Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
