<HEADLINE> Escartin Wins Tour of Catalonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Fernando Escartin led
compatriots to a 1-2-3 finish at the Tour of Catalonia cycling
race which ended in Adnorra on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Escartin won the race by just two seconds after sticking by
second-placed compatriot Angel Casero throughout the final stage,
which was won by Sergei Uchakov of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Mikel Zarrabeitia, a further 24 seconds back in the
overall standings, finished third.
</P>
<P>
Escartin, the best-classified Spaniard in both the Tour of
France and Tour of Spain last year, had taken the lead in
Wednesday's tough mountain stage.
</P>
<P>
Uchakov won the final stage in a time of five hours, seven
minutes and 47 seconds. He was followed by Austrian Henk Vogels
and Frenchman Frederic Moncassin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
