<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Criticizes Industrialized Nations for Not </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Ukrain's Foreign Minister
Hennadi Udovenko today criticized the world's leading
industrialized nations for not honoring their promises to help his
country from the 1986 nuclear disaster at Chernobyl.
</P>
<P>
"We are still victims of Chernobyl. We deal with all problems
alone, without any substantial financial assistance," Udovenko
said at a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
The Ukraine foreign minister is attending the five-day Earth
Summit at the United Nations headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko said that the world's industrial giants have been slow
in providing technical advice and financial assistance to
Chernobyl, where a reactor exploded, killing 32 people within
months and sending a radioactive cloud over Europe.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine officials said at the Earth Summit that their country
spends some 1 billion U.S. dollars a year to minimize the impact
of the Chernobyl explosion, the world's worst nuclear accident.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
