<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street pulled back
modestly today as investors felt some uncertainty before next
week's key Federal Reserve meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 35.73 points to 7,654.25.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with the volume reaching 499.78
million shares, down from 603.03 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 5.30 to 883.69, and
the NYSE composite index fell 1.97 to 460.93.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 9.87 to 1,436.37, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 3.14 to 616.10.
</P>
<P>
The Labor Department reported that the number of first-time
claims for jobless benefits fell more than expected last week.
</P>
<P>
Interest rates on the bond market rose again, posing some
pressure on the stock market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
